  <h1>🎱 Gingo – Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="meta">Effective date: 2 May 2026 &nbsp;|&nbsp; Last updated: 2 May 2026</p>

  <p>This Privacy Policy describes how the Gingo app ("the App") handles your information. Gingo is developed and maintained by GraVicAnt Inc.</p>

  <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>Gingo does <strong>not</strong> collect, transmit, or share any personal information. The App does not require you to create an account, log in, or provide any personal details.</p>

  <h2>2. Data Storage</h2>
  <p>All data you enter into the App — including bingo draw records, predictions, and settings — is stored <strong>exclusively on your device</strong> using local storage. This data never leaves your device and is never sent to any server, cloud service, or third party.</p>

  <h2>3. Internet Access</h2>
  <p>Gingo does <strong>not</strong> require an internet connection to function. The App operates entirely offline. No network requests are made at any time.</p>

  <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
  <p>Gingo does not integrate with any third-party analytics, advertising, tracking, or data collection services.</p>

  <h2>5. Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>Gingo is not directed at children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect any information from children. Since the App collects no information from any user, no special provisions for children are required beyond this statement.</p>

  <h2>6. Data Security</h2>
  <p>Since all data remains on your device and no data is transmitted externally, the security of your data is governed by your device's own security features (screen lock, encryption, etc.).</p>

  <h2>7. Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>If we make changes to this Privacy Policy, we will update the "Last updated" date at the top of this page. Continued use of the App after any changes constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.</p>

